SQL (structured query language) is a standard language for storing, manipulating and retrieving data in databases.

Statements:

SELECT: statement is used to select data from a database.
eg. Select * 
    From table_name;
    
SELECT DISTINCT: statement is used to return only distinct (different) values.
eg. Select distinct column_1
    From table_name;
    
WHERE: it is used to filter record.
eg. Select column_1
    From table_name
    Where some_condition;

ORDER BY: it is used to sort the result by asc or desc order.
eg. Select column_1
    From table_name
    Where some_condition
    Order by column_1 asc or desc -> asc by default
